      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:1:1:1:28",
      "text": [
        " قَالَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ( صلى الله عليه وآله ) إِذَا رَأَيْتُمُ الرَّجُلَ كَثِيرَ الصَّلَاةِ كَثِيرَ الصِّيَامِ فَلَا تُبَاهُوا بِهِ حَتَّى تَنْظُرُوا كَيْفَ عَقْلُهُ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "A number of our companions, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad, from someone who raised it, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘Rasool-Allah<sup>saww</sup> said: ‘Whenever you see the man as being of abundant in <span class=\"iTxt\">Salāt</span>, abundant in Fasts, so do not be boasting with him until you look at how (good) his intellect is’’."
        ]
      }
    }
